.TH "csio_shost_init" 9 "csio_shost_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
csio_shost_init \- Create and initialize the lnode module.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct csio_lnode *" csio_shost_init
.BI "(struct csio_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "bool probe "  ","
.BI "struct csio_lnode *pln "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
The HW module.
.IP "dev" 12
The device associated with this invocation.
.IP "probe" 12
Called from probe context or not?
.IP "pln" 12
Parent lnode if any.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates lnode structure via scsi_host_alloc, initializes
shost, initializes lnode module and registers with SCSI ML
via scsi_host_add. This function is shared between physical and
virtual node ports.
